$timescale 1ns $end
$comment
  MDIO Pro decoder error-detection fixture.
  Seven frame groups:
    (a) Clean C22 read              (green)
    (b) Frame with ST=11            (RED — Invalid ST pattern)
    (c) Clean C22 write             (green)
    (d) C22 read bad turnaround     (RED — Bad turnaround)
    (e) Clean C45 write             (green)
    (f) Frame truncated mid-data    (RED — Truncated MDIO)
    (g) Frame with X on PHYAD       (RED — X/Z value on MDIO)
  Each red transaction is bracketed by a green control frame
  so the comparison is obvious in the transaction table.
  Regenerate via:
    dart run tool/generate_mdio_error_fixture.dart
$end
$scope module tb $end
$var wire 1 ! MDC $end
$var wire 1 " MDIO $end
$upscope $end
$enddefinitions $end
$dumpvars
0!
1"
$end
